  "title": "Facility Maintenance Engineer",
  "description": "<p>Roles & Responsibilities</p><p>ALG is currently recruiting for Facility Maintenance Engineers<strong> </strong>for our client based in the west side of Singapore. This is an exciting opportunity for a 2-year contract.<br /><br />Our client is known for designing, manufacturing, and servicing systems and components for the aerospace and defence industries. </p><p>Working Days: Monday - Saturday, from 9am to 6pm</p><p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong>:</p><ul><li>Troubleshooting and corrective maintenance </li><li>Routine and preventive maintenance activities </li><li>Assisting our service engineer during maintenance and service works </li><li>Coordinating effectively with relevant parties (clients, vendors, and internal teams)</li><li>Perform quarterly cleaning of the equipment onsite </li><li>Experience with turnstiles, kiosks, drop-arm barrier, Wi-Fi Access Points, cabling, UPS, and door access reader</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong>:</p><ul><li>Training will be provided but Engineer must be well-versed in BACS 2.0 systems and maintenance practices </li><li>Hands-on actual M&E related work </li><li>Engineer needs to be based onsite during working hours </li><li>Proficient in both spoken and written English. </li><li>Able to do OT</li></ul><p>If you meet the above qualifications and are interested in this role, <strong>APPLY NOW!</strong> Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.<br /></p><p>EA License Number: 11C4379 | Registration Number: R22105299</p>",
